Time Series of active days

Lets take a look at the number of active Chinese vessels (more than 1 position with speed > 1) per day from 2013-2015.

Does the number of active vessels increase in other regions because of the moratoria?

Who is unaffected by the moratoria?

There are 12454 vessels that remain active inside Chinas EEZ during the moratoria. Their size distribution looks like:

The gear types of these vessels are:

general_vessel_type n
NA 9165
Trawler 2113
Seiner 992
Tug/Pilot/Supply 136
Longliner 47
Fish Carrier 1

How many vessels are affected by the moratoria?

Comparing the active vessels in Chinas EEZ one month before and after the moratoria with those active during the moratoria we can estimate the number of vessels affected by this policy.

There are 4164 vessels that were active within Chinas EEZ one month before or after the moratoria but that are not during the moratoria.

Of those, 4062 are not see at all during the moratoria and 102 were displaced to other regions. The question then is: what are these vessels doing? where did they go?
